==English==
'''[[there]] and [[back]]'''
===Pronunciation & Etymology===
See separate entries for '''[[there]]''' and '''[[back]]'''.

===Idiom===
*An idiom referring to a [[round trip]] journey, going to a place (or state of mind) and returning.
*:''(It took me about 20 minutes there and back)''
*:''(You don't need to tell me about depression. I've been there and back)''